Interface QueueADT<E>

Record Components:
E - The elements that the list holds.
public interface QueueADT<E>
QueueADT.java
Version:
1.0, 2025-10-22

The QueueADT interface is designed to be used as a basis for the Queue data structure that will be developed in the CPRG304 E2025 class at SAIT.

This is an interface that describes a list data type where insertions can only be made at the end of the list and removals can only be done at the beginning of the list.
Author:
Chris Hanlon

      void enqueue(E object)
      Inserts an Element to the end of the queue.

      Precondition: A queue has been created.

      Postcondition: The Element is added to the end of the queue.

      Parameters:
      object - The Element you are trying to insert into the queue.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - The element you are trying to insert is not compatible with the queue.
